{
  "stem": "26576.4",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yeah.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So when-- how did it come that I decided-- you know, actual people ask me how could you, after such a terrible war, and after such terrible things, how could you wanted to stay on in Poland and study?",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But, you know, when you are young, you don't think like that.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I knew that we have struggled years in Siberia and later on, years in [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And I wanted to become something.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And I knew that if I will not stay on in Poland, I knew that if I will move, I will lose the language.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And it was hard enough as it was, because, you've got to realize, one has to realize, how many languages I went through.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I came to Russia without a word of Russian.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And then when I came out of Russia, I forgot Polish, because Polish, although it was my number one language-- but if you don't speak a language for five, six years, you completely-- so you lose track.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And when I came back to Poland, there were no Polish books. 1945, when we came to Katowice, you couldn't find a Polish book.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And I started to read German.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So for one year, I read only German books.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I then-- I thought to myself, if I have again now to lose and start with a new language, then I really won't be able to do it, because I was thinking, at that stage, that I'm getting old and I have to the something in order to finish my studies.",
      "word_count": 52
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And as it happened, 1946 was the year, really, that I blossomed.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "All of us, the ones that came back, because Poland was-- we would get parcels from-- from United States.",
      "word_count": 19
    }
  ],
